caption: Omg. Like really, good Lord these were good! The food (empanadas and arepa) was just excellent and the popsicle we had was fantastic. Pricing is quite reasonable. The proprietor is a super nice guy and was really great to interact with. You MUST order in advance by texting the phone number. You will be sent the menu for the day - it changes based on ingredients and such - and you can text back your order. It is a busy place but It worked seamlessly for us. We will DEFINITELY be ordering again. Could not recommend more highly.
Absolutely amazing food! Great find in Waikiki

Don't pass this place up, this dude knows what's he's doing. Easily the best Cuban sandwich and empanadas I've ever had. No ordering there, call or text ahead to get his daily menu and he has it ready when you get there, it's pretty awesome. Almost makes you feel like you're using a password at a speakeasy. And he's a super nice guy as well.
Absolutely the best food in town. Make sure you text his number to get the menu each night. Alex is an awesome guy 10/10 would recommend this spot

This is an awesome spot! I had the all the empanadas of the day and they were all excellent. The real stand out for me was the blood sausage. It's was herbaceous and super fresh. You also can't leave without one of his handmade pops! It was stupidly good.
Excellent Colombian Food!! Alex was very friendly and welcoming. Empanadas were delicious as well as Arepas. He made our night. Recommended!!!

Alex is the man. He seriously works ridiculously hard to make sure every customer has a great experience. The deliciousness of his empanadas, arepas, and sauces are unrivaled by any restaurants in the area. Highly recommend going here at least once during your time in Hawaii. I'm from Miami and am used to many latin American food options and I can confirm that his recipes are uniquely authentic. This guy deserves his own restaurant chain. Great service, even better food, a block away from the beach.

Found this place mentioned in a blog on pinterest I found. Googled it and saw the awesome reviews. I even sent it to my friend to see if she wanted something. It lives up to the hype. I called to see if cards were accepted (yes cards are accepted) but I didn't get an answer. He sent a text back with the menu for the night and when he would open. I ended up ordering 2 Colombian vegan potato empanadas, 2 cheese lover empanadas and 1 arepa con queso. My friend got the Cubano. Everything was absolutely delicious. The sauces were icing on the cake. I may go back again before I head back to Florida. Alex was also a pleasure to talk to. Thanks Alex!!

Loved everything we got! Order the empanadas and the hot dog, SO GOOD. The sauces make it too. The pink, white, and green sauce were very flavorful. Also tried the ice pops. Think elevated big otter pop from real fruit juices. Lemonade and watermelon were our favorite.  Order ahead and pick up. You can also order frozen empanadas or tamales to take home just makes sure to order early so he can have them ready.

**CALL OR TEXT YOUR ORDER IN ADVANCE** Amazing corn empanadas I will remember them forever. He makes them fresh for you and serves it with a wonderful personality. Please please he highly recommends calling to order in advance so you don't have to wait from 15mins to an hour or run out.

When we got there we were able to order sofrito chicken, vegan potato and beef and potato. The sofrito one was so delicious and so full of flavor! All of them were really good. This is no fast food truck, it's made to order air fried empanadas. If available, Alex also makes Cubano Sandwiches he bakes his own bread. So if you're not wanting to wait I suggest to call him up to check on the wait times for the food, and to see what he will have available for food. This spot is definitely worth the wait!
All his food is wonderful. He makes everything from scratch, so there is a bit of a wait. You can call or text beforehand and order if you don't want to wait.

I had a really long day of travel to Hawaii and then upon my arrival, I realized I made a reservation at the wrong hotel. These were first-world problems to be sure, but I was definitely not having the most auspicious start to my trip... until I decided to walk around my hotel and found Mami's Empanadas. The wait was a little long, but the chief empanada officer was quite upfront about that before I ordered and the food was well worth the wait. Really delicious on their own, the empanadas are taken to the flavor stratosphere by a combination of spicy green sauce and white garlic sauce.

The Chef, Alex, is extremely passionate about his empenada cart and the food that he serves out of it.  The menu of empenadas available changes daily.  He opens at night and tends to sell out.  If you ask "whats good?", Alex will inform you that "It doesn't matter, it's all good... What are you in the mood for?"  He uses an air fryer so they come out hot and crispy, not oily.  He makes his own bread for the Cuban Hotdogs.  Wait times vary from no wait to where you put your order in (or call it) and pick it up later.  I'm always able to get pretty fast service.  He accepts cash AND card!  Please like this review to help uncover this hidden gem.  Tip: Park on the street in one of the availabe EWA Hotel spaces.  They are reserved but you'll be able to supervise your car while you eat.  Its a one way street so if the toe truck comes run for the car and offer the tow operator an Empanada and it's settled.

Alright folks, here’s my two cents, the empanadas are on point, a must have, and the owner seems like a good guy hustling to make a living. Why not five stars you might ask, well because regardless of if there’s two people outside his “truck” or ten he will always say he’s busy, and he moves around inside like a mad mad. The issue as to why he’s so stressed as I watched him for the thirty minutes it took to get out food is that everything comes out of the fridge/ freezer and he puts each order into one infrared style dome cooker. These items are cooked to order from cold or frozen, and that just takes time, eventually he runs out of space causing a backlog. I’m unsure of why he can’t run a second cooker, but there seems to be some pageantry that goes into convincing people he’s busier than he his, simply to stall for the cooking time of these pre made then frozen delights. If you want to try this place which you should, then drop him a text message and ask him to order in advance, take a nice slow walk to the nearest ABC store for a cold beverage and when you get there to collect your 4 to 6 empanadas per person you’ll be happy you did and can avoid the performance that reminded me of someone selling fake perfume or Rolex’s on a subway car.
Excellent Colombian empanadas. Also serves Cuban sandwiches and Colombian-style hot dogs. The owner is very busy so it takes a little while but not too long. Excellent! Highly recommended.

This place deserves 12 stars. It's a small food trailer tucked on a side street but the best and rarest gems are always hidden. The food is fantastic, and the service makes you feel glad that you came. They usually have about 4-6 flavors of empanadas, and they change daily, so your tastebuds experience a new treat every time you go. Do yourself a favor and accept all the sauces they recommend, they are homemade, authentic, and phenomenal. They also serve arepas, which are equally awesome. The one menu item that is always on the menu (if you get there early enough before they've sold out, that is) is the cubano sandwich. Order one - you'll instantly discover why they sell out daily. They also serve sodas from Latin America that aren't available in your local grocery store, so order one with your meal for a truly international experience right here in Waikīkī!
